# Dev Services Registry
# Format: NAME|TYPE|PORT|START_CMD|STOP_CMD|HEALTH_CHECK
#
# TYPE:
#   launchd   - managed by launchctl (uses START_CMD as plist label)
#   process   - managed by start/stop commands directly
#   ollama    - special: ollama serve
#
# HEALTH_CHECK: a command that exits 0 if healthy, non-zero if not
#   use "port" to just check if the port is listening
#   use "none" if no check possible

SurrealDB|launchd|6000|com.surrealdb.server|com.surrealdb.server|port
Ollama|launchd|11434|com.ollama.server|com.ollama.server|port

# ── Web Dev (ephemeral — start manually, tracked for visibility) ──────────────
# These are not auto-started. `dev` surfaces them if they're running.
Arc|ephemeral|3000|none|none|port

# ── MCP Servers (7000–7099) ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Add rows here as you wire up MCP servers
# Example:
# MyMCP|launchd|7000|com.example.mcp|com.example.mcp|port
